e=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104adh1665702963734.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/adh1665702963734.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/adh1665702963734.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"adh1665702963734\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Support for Unicode in the SYB Connector\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"adh1665702963734__support_for_unicode_in_the_syb_connector_172837\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Uniface SYB connector can support Unicode. By default, Unicode support is disabled.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adh1665702963734__p_d58985e1_d58986e1_d58987e1\">When Unicode is enabled, Unicode characters can be used in:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26414e1_d26415e1_d26416e1\">Fields with wide character packing codes (such as W10, SW* )\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26417e1_d26418e1_d26419e1\">SQL Workbench and the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26420e1_d26421e1_d26422e1\">Sybase stored procedures\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26423e1_d26424e1_d26425e1\">Uniface Service Stored Procedures (SSP)\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note important note_important\" id=\"adh1665702963734__p_d58988e1_d58989e1_d58990e1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Important:</span> Unicode is not supported in table names, column names, or user names and passwords.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adh1665702963734__p_d58991e1_d58992e1_d58993e1\">You can enable and configure Unicode support by setting connector options in the application assignment file. The following connector options and settings determine where Unicode characters can be used:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26426e1_d26427e1_d26428e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tlc1665702735327.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlc1665702735327.html\" title=\"Enable or disable Unicode support in the SYB connector.\">unicode</a>\n</code>—enables Unicode for fields with wide-character packing codes. By default, this is limited to characters in the Basic Multilingual Plane (BMP).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26429e1_d26430e1_d26431e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xyw1665702963805.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xyw1665702963805.html\" title=\"When Unicode support is enabled, allow the full range of Unicode characters to be stored in W packing code fields.\">smp</a>\n</code>—extends Unicode support to include the Supplementary Multilingual Plane (SMP) in W packing codes.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26432e1_d26433e1_d26434e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tke1665702734474.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tke1665702734474.html\" title=\"Set default character set used by the Sybase open client.\">charset</a> utf8</code>—enables Unicode characters to be used in SQL Workbench and the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26435e1_d26436e1_d26437e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ozf1665702734970.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ozf1665702734970.html\" title=\"Adds double quotes around field and table names and sets the Sybase option quoted_identifier on.\">keyword</a>\n</code>—distinguishes between data and column names, so that Unicode can be used in the SQL Workbench and the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"adh1665702963734__li_d26438e1_d26439e1_d26440e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmh1665702657664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmh1665702657664.html\" title=\"Set or return the value of $DEF_CHARSET, which defines the character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.\">$def_charset</a>=UTF8</code>—ensures that Unicode is also supported in Uniface Service Stored Procedures (SSP) and Sybase stored procedures.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jtr1665702874645.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Support for Unicode</a><p>Uniface supports Unicode in the user interface, database storage and retrieval, sorting, case conversion, and data exchange. Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azs1665703222737.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$DEF_CHARSET</a><p>Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525632\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525632\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Support for Unicode in the SYB Connector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Support for Unicode in the SYB Connector The Uniface SYB connector can support Unicode. By default, Unicode support is disabled. When Unicode is enabled, Unicode characters can be used in: Fields with wide character packing codes (such as W10, SW* ) SQL Workbench and the sql ProcScript statement Sybase stored procedures Uniface Service Stored Procedures (SSP) Important: Unicode is not supported in table names, column names, or user names and passwords. You can enable and configure Unicode support by setting connector options in the application assignment file. The following connector options and settings determine where Unicode characters can be used: unicode —enables Unicode for fields with wide-character packing codes. By default, this is limited to characters in the Basic Multilingual Plane (BMP). smp —extends Unicode support to include the Supplementary Multilingual Plane (SMP) in W packing codes. charset utf8 —enables Unicode characters to be used in SQL Workbench and the sql ProcScript statement. keyword —distinguishes between data and column names, so that Unicode can be used in the SQL Workbench and the sql ProcScript statement. $def_charset =UTF8 —ensures that Unicode is also supported in Uniface Service Stored Procedures (SSP) and Sybase stored procedures. Related Links Uniface Support for Unicode Uniface supports Unicode in the user interface, database storage and retrieval, sorting, case conversion, and data exchange. Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set. $DEF_CHARSET Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}